CRITICAL: For data queries (show, list, display, view), ALWAYS use "dataframe" type!

Rules:
- Data display queries → { "type": "dataframe", "value": pd.DataFrame(...) }
- Count queries → { "type": "number", "value": 123 }
- Text responses → { "type": "string", "value": "text" }

Examples:
{ "type": "dataframe", "value": pd.DataFrame({"Rider Name": ["John", "Jane"], "City": ["Karachi", "Lahore"]}) }
{ "type": "number", "value": 150 }

{% elif output_type == "dataframe" %}
type (must be "dataframe"), value must be pd.DataFrame with clean columns.
Example: { "type": "dataframe", "value": pd.DataFrame({"Column1": ["value1"], "Column2": ["value2"]}) }

{% elif output_type == "string" %}
type (must be "string"), value must be string.

{% elif output_type == "number" %}
type (must be "number"), value must be int or float.

{% elif output_type == "plot" %}
type (must be "plot"), value must be string path.
{% endif %}
